        "created_at": "2021-03-30T19:05:55.118Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Same for iOS, too:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"25302\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/b4bc9f/48.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/image-crop-and-image-zoom-sending-media/25302\">Image Crop and Image Zoom - Sending Media</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/ios-feature-requests/19\"><span data-category-id=\"19\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #2D8B39; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF; --parent-category-badge-color: #83B72A;\" data-parent-category-id=\"17\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --has-parent\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">iOS Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    Hello \nI have tried several searches for this and cannot find anything related (advanced apologies if there is such). \nIn iOS, when sending a photo in Signal, you select the image to be sent but may want to zoom into detail or, crucially, edit it. There arenâ€™t many editing options currently, however there is one to â€˜blurâ€™. \nRecently, I have been wanting to send images but blur out (redact) some confidential information. There are two issues here: \n\nThere is no width selector for the â€˜eraserâ€™ andâ€¦\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n\n<p>I got the impression from others that this was less of an ordeal with Android, however?</p>\n<p>Perhaps not. Itâ€™s largely unusable on iOS as it currently stands. I am having to edit photos outside of Signal for redactions and edits.</p>",
